      "source": [
        "# üå± AI Tutor for Green Skill Development and Sustainability Awareness\n",
        "\n",
        "# -----------------------------\n",
        "# STEP 1 ‚Äî Install libraries\n",
        "# -----------------------------\n",
        "!pip install openai pandas matplotlib\n",
        "\n",
        "# -----------------------------\n",
        "# STEP 2 ‚Äî Import libraries\n",
        "# -----------------------------\n",
        "import pandas as pd\n",
        "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
        "import openai\n",
        "from google.colab import files\n",
        "import random # Import random for quiz question selection\n",
        "\n",
        "# -----------------------------\n",
        "# STEP 3 ‚Äî Create dataset automatically\n",
        "# -----------------------------\n",
        "data = \"\"\"Topic,Description,Quiz_Question,Correct_Answer,Difficulty\n",
        "Renewable Energy,Energy from natural sources like sun, wind, and water,Which energy source is renewable?,Solar Energy,Easy\n",
        "Waste Management,Proper disposal and recycling of waste,What is the 3R principle?,Reduce, Reuse, Recycle,Medium\n",
        "Water Conservation,Efficient use of water resources,Name one method of saving water,Rainwater Harvesting,Easy\n",
        "Climate Change,Global temperature rise due to pollution,What gas causes global warming?,Carbon Dioxide,Hard\n",
        "Sustainable Agriculture,Eco-friendly farming practices,Which fertilizer is eco-friendly?,Organic Compost,Medium\n",
        "Biodiversity,Variety of living organisms on Earth,Why is biodiversity important?,It maintains ecological balance,Medium\n",
        "Green Technology,Technology that reduces environmental impact,Give an example of green technology,Solar Panels,Medium\n",
        "Recycling,Converting waste into reusable material,What is the benefit of recycling?,Reduces waste and saves resources,Easy\n",
        "Pollution Control,Preventing harmful substances in environment,Which device helps reduce air pollution?,Air Filter,Medium\n",
        "Eco-friendly Transport,Transport causing less pollution,Name one eco-friendly vehicle,Electric Vehicle,Easy\n",
        "Composting,Decomposing organic material into fertilizer,What is composting?,Recycling organic waste,Easy\n",
        "Carbon Footprint,Total greenhouse gas emissions by an individual or organization,How can you reduce your carbon footprint?,Use public transport,Medium\n",
        "Sustainable Fashion,Clothing made in an eco-friendly way,What is a benefit of sustainable fashion?,Reduces environmental impact of clothing production,Medium\n",
        "Green Building,Construction using sustainable materials and practices,What is a key feature of green building?,Energy efficiency,Medium\n",
        "Circular Economy,System where resources are reused and recycled,What is the goal of a circular economy?,Minimize waste and resource depletion,Hard\n",
        "\"\"\"\n",
        "\n",
        "with open(\"green_skills.csv\", \"w\") as f:\n",
        "    f.write(data)\n",
        "\n",
        "print(\"‚úÖ green_skills.csv created successfully!\\n\")\n",
        "\n",
        "# -----------------------------\n",
        "# STEP 4 ‚Äî Load dataset\n",
        "# -----------------------------\n",
        "try:\n",
        "    df = pd.read_csv(\"green_skills.csv\")\n",
        "    print(\"üìò Dataset Preview:\")\n",
        "    display(df.head())\n",
        "except FileNotFoundError:\n",
        "    print(\"‚ùå Dataset file not found! Please upload green_skills.csv to your Colab environment or ensure it's created correctly.\")\n",
        "    raise SystemExit\n",
        "\n",
        "# -----------------------------\n",
        "# STEP 5 ‚Äî Set your OpenAI key\n",
        "# -----------------------------\n",
        "openai.api_key = input(\"\\nüîë Enter your OpenAI API key: \")\n",
        "\n",
        "# -----------------------------\n",
        "# STEP 6 ‚Äî AI explanation function\n",
        "# -----------------------------\n",
        "def ai_explain(topic):\n",
        "    prompt = f\"Explain the importance of {topic} in sustainability and green skill development in 100 simple words.\"\n",
        "    try:\n",
        "        response = openai.ChatCompletion.create(\n",
        "            model=\"gpt-3.5-turbo\",\n",
        "            messages=[{\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": prompt}]\n",
        "        )\n",
        "        return response[\"choices\"][0][\"message\"][\"content\"]\n",
        "    except Exception as e:\n",
        "        return f\"‚ö†Ô∏è AI explanation unavailable: {e}\"\n",
        "\n",
        "# -----------------------------\n",
        "# STEP 7 ‚Äî Tutor interaction and Quiz\n",
        "# -----------------------------\n",
        "print(\"\\nüåç Welcome to AI Tutor for Green Skill Development üå±\")\n",
        "print(\"------------------------------------------------------\")\n",
        "\n",
        "print(\"\\nAvailable Topics:\")\n",
        "for i, topic in enumerate(df[\"Topic\"], 1):\n",
        "    print(f\"{i}. {topic}\")\n",
        "\n",
        "try:\n",
        "    choice = int(input(\"\\nEnter topic number to learn: \"))\n",
        "    topic = df.iloc[choice - 1][\"Topic\"]\n",
        "    desc = df.iloc[choice - 1][\"Description\"]\n",
        "except (ValueError, IndexError):\n",
        "    print(\"‚ùå Invalid choice. Please restart and choose a valid topic.\")\n",
        "    raise SystemExit\n",
        "\n",
        "print(f\"\\nüìò Topic Selected: {topic}\")\n",
        "print(f\"üìÑ Description: {desc}\")\n",
        "\n",
        "print(\"\\nü§ñ AI Tutor says:\")\n",
        "print(ai_explain(topic))\n",
        "\n",
        "# Quiz Section integrated here\n",
        "print(\"\\nüìù Short Quiz Section:\")\n",
        "# Select 5 random questions, ensuring there are at least 5 questions\n",
        "num_quiz_questions = min(5, len(df))\n",
        "questions = df.sample(num_quiz_questions)\n",
        "score = 0\n",
        "\n",
        "for i, q in enumerate(questions.itertuples(), 1):\n",
        "    print(f\"\\nQ{i}: {q.Quiz_Question}\")\n",
        "    ans = input(\"Your answer: \")\n",
        "    if ans.strip().lower() == q.Correct_Answer.strip().lower():\n",
        "        print(\"‚úÖ Correct!\")\n",
        "        score += 1\n",
        "    else:\n",
        "        print(f\"‚ùå Wrong! Correct answer: {q.Correct_Answer}\")\n",
        "\n",
        "# -----------------------------\n",
        "# STEP 8 ‚Äî Show Quiz Results (Bar Chart and Pie Chart)\n",
        "# -----------------------------\n",
        "print(\"\\nüéØ Quiz Completed!\")\n",
        "print(f\"‚úÖ Correct Answers: {score}\")\n",
        "print(f\"‚ùå Wrong Answers: {num_quiz_questions - score}\")\n",
        "\n",
        "# Bar Chart\n",
        "plt.figure(figsize=(6, 4))\n",
        "plt.bar([\"Correct\", \"Wrong\"], [score, num_quiz_questions - score], color=['#4CAF50', '#FF6F61'])\n",
        "plt.title(f\"Quiz Results - {topic}\")\n",
        "plt.xlabel(\"Result\")\n",
        "plt.ylabel(\"Number of Questions\")\n",
        "plt.show()\n",
        "\n",
        "# Pie Chart\n",
        "labels = ['Correct', 'Wrong']\n",
        "sizes = [score, num_quiz_questions - score]\n",
        "colors = ['#4CAF50', '#FF6F61']\n",
        "explode = (0.1, 0) # explode the 'Correct' slice\n",
        "\n",
        "plt.figure(figsize=(6,6))\n",
        "plt.pie(\n",
        "    sizes,\n",
        "    labels=labels,\n",
        "    colors=colors,\n",
        "    autopct='%1.1f%%',\n",
        "    startangle=140, # Changed startangle for better visualization\n",
        "    shadow=True,\n",
        "    explode=explode\n",
        ")\n",
        "plt.title(\"üåé AI Tutor Quiz Result - Green Skill Awareness\", fontsize=14)\n",
        "plt.axis('equal') # Equal aspect ratio ensures that pie is drawn as a circle.\n",
        "plt.savefig(\"quiz_result_piechart.png\") # Saving the pie chart\n",
        "plt.show()\n",
        "\n",
        "print(\"\\nüìä Pie Chart saved as 'quiz_result_piechart.png' ‚úÖ\")"
      ],
      "execution_count": 4,

        "## Prepare data\n",
        "\n",
        "### Subtask:\n",
        "Handle missing values in the 'Difficulty' column, encode it into numerical labels, and split the data into training and testing sets.\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "5702aa6b"
      },
      "source": [
        "**Reasoning**:\n",
        "Check for and handle missing values in the 'Difficulty' column, encode the 'Difficulty' column into numerical labels, define features and target, and then split the data into training and testing sets.\n",
        "\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
        },
        "id": "a648cccd",
        "outputId": "f76a3095-a645-4adf-a12d-52b920a8995e"
      },
      "source": [
        "# Check for missing values in 'Difficulty' and drop rows with missing values\n",
        "initial_rows = len(df)\n",
        "df.dropna(subset=['Difficulty'], inplace=True)\n",
        "rows_after_dropping = len(df)\n",
        "print(f\"Dropped {initial_rows - rows_after_dropping} rows with missing 'Difficulty' values.\")\n",
        "\n",
        "# Import and apply LabelEncoder\n",
        "from sklearn.preprocessing import LabelEncoder\n",
        "le = LabelEncoder()\n",
        "df['Difficulty_Encoded'] = le.fit_transform(df['Difficulty'])\n",
        "\n",
        "# Define features (X) and target (y)\n",
        "# Using 'Description' and 'Quiz_Question' as features, combined\n",
        "df['Text_Features'] = df['Description'] + ' ' + df['Quiz_Question']\n",
        "X = df['Text_Features']\n",
        "y = df['Difficulty_Encoded']\n",
        "\n",
        "# Import and apply train_test_split\n",
        "from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split\n",
        "X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(X, y, test_size=0.25, random_state=42, stratify=y)\n",
        "\n",
        "print(\"\\nData successfully processed and split.\")\n",
        "print(f\"X_train shape: {X_train.shape}\")\n",
        "print(f\"X_test shape: {X_test.shape}\")\n",
        "print(f\"y_train shape: {y_train.shape}\")\n",
        "print(f\"y_test shape: {y_test.shape}\")"
      ],

        "## Feature extraction\n",

        "outputId": "97d8fd3a-8d23-4fef-b1a1-077fa1fed6bf"
      },
      "source": [
        "from sklearn.metrics import confusion_matrix, accuracy_score, precision_score, recall_score, f1_score\n",
        "\n",
        "# Make predictions on the test data\n",
        "y_pred = model.predict(X_test_tfidf)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Generate the confusion matrix\n",
        "cm = confusion_matrix(y_test, y_pred)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Print the confusion matrix\n",
        "print(\"Confusion Matrix:\")\n",
        "print(cm)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Calculate and print classification metrics\n",
        "accuracy = accuracy_score(y_test, y_pred)\n",
        "precision = precision_score(y_test, y_pred, average='weighted', zero_division=0)\n",
        "recall = recall_score(y_test, y_pred, average='weighted', zero_division=0)\n",
        "f1 = f1_score(y_test, y_pred, average='weighted', zero_division=0)\n",
        "\n",
        "print(\"\\nClassification Metrics:\")\n",
        "print(f\"Accuracy: {accuracy:.4f}\")\n",
        "print(f\"Precision: {precision:.4f}\")\n",
        "print(f\"Recall: {recall:.4f}\")\n",
        "print(f\"F1-score: {f1:.4f}\")"
